title: Feet on the Streets against all things trump
description:
Are you tired of sitting home and feeling helpless about the current regime?

Our little group is growing - come join us! Everyone is welcome!

This is becoming a regular spot for our voices to be heard and for the unengaged to see "regular people" fighting for democracy consistently.

We are getting lots of positive beeps and encouragement from the community, especially the foot traffic - they have been very welcoming!*

Just being with like-minded people is helpful and it's inspiring.   It's absolutely the antidote to our fear and frustration -- we instead turn it into action!

Bring a sign and come on down - we always have an extra sign or two, so don't let that stop you from joining us !

Meantime, take heart ... "tomorrow, there will be more of us ..."

*PLEASE NOTE:  We do NOT engage with the hecklers!   They are getting bolder.  We literally ignore them - let them be the ones to escalate.  

Other organizations are advising that every other protester sit down peacefully when aggression takes over ... this way, the police will have a clear view of who is exactly causing the problems!

Also, VIDEOTAPE it ... have your cameras/videos ready to tape immediately ... the cop who happened to be at the right spot reminded us that otherwise, it's he said/she said.  VIDEOTAPING is key!  If you can do it without their knowledge, all the better - they get incredibly MAD when they are being taped!  BE VIGILANT AND BE SMART -- 

I know it's easier said than done, but we must just ignore them - they are doing it ON PURPOSE to incite us into starting something -- which is exactly why we must REFUSE TO GIVE THEM THAT HONOR!    Shun them ... turn your backs on them ... ignore them 

**Ask about our other local events on different dates and different corners or just search Chula Vista right here for other links!**

Beeeeeeep Beeeeeeeeeep!!!

See you on the streets!
accessibility_notes: We are also going to start a Food Drive while we are there - for now, feel free to bring any shelf stable items - we will make sure they get to a food bank to be shared ... more to come, but let's start here!

title: Sign the Petition to Overturn SB1 and Save Higher Education in Ohio
description:
At the May Executive Committee meeting, the Greene County Democratic Party endorsed the referendum campaign to overturn SB1.  
We are collecting signatures at our HQ every Wednesday and Thursday from 10-2, and at many other events and festivals. 

Why do we oppose SB 1?  Because this bill will fundamentally change our public universities for the worse. 

SB 1 will restrict what professors can teach. It will silence important discussions on issues like climate change and current events. It will dismantle diversity programs that make our campuses welcoming for everyone. It threatens entire academic departments, weakens university workers’ rights, and effectively ends meaningful tenure for professors. 

SB 1 will drive away students, professors, and valuable research dollars. It will hurt Ohio tourism and cost us jobs.

Before this bill was passed by our legislature and signed by our governor, there was a LOT of opposition to it. Over 1000 Ohioans provided testimony against it, while only 14 supported it. 

 That's why we're asking you to sign this petition. Let's put SB 1 on the ballot and let the voters of Ohio decide.

After flipping the VA House of Delegates in 2023 by 975 votes, we must protect our Democratic majority to continue safeguarding democracy, especially with the growing threats coming from the federal government. As public interest is usually higher during gubernatorial elections, this provides us an opportunity to reach more voters, educate them around the importance of their state legislature and direct their attention to our candidate down ballot.

We identify supporters and let them know why their vote matters, speak with undecided voters, and recruit local volunteers. We provide our candidate’s campaign critical information about the district’s constituents which can then influence the campaign’s allocation of resources.

description:
Help Michael Feggans win re-election while testing your knowledge of random facts all in the cozy confines of a gorgeous community space.

In 2023, Michael Feggans flipped House District 97 from a red to a blue seat in one of the most competitive races in Virginia and got right to work, earning the 2024 Climate All-Star Award from the Chesapeake Climate Action Network Fund and 2024 Legislative Rookie of the Year from the Virginia Education Association. Michael Feggans was raised for most of his life in the West Kempsville portion of Virginia Beach. A proud product of the Virginia Beach Public School system, he graduated from Tallwood High School and immediately enlisted in the U.S. Air Force to pursue a career that would provide him the opportunity to become an innovative leader. title: May General Meeting - Picnic 🧺
description:
## Your Voice Matters, And So Does Ice Cream! 🍨


Our next General Meeting is coming up and this one’s a little sweeter. 

Haven’t been to a meeting yet? No better time to ‘break the ice’ than an ice cream social!

🗓 Thursday, May 22 at 5:30pm

📍 Heaven for Kids Park (next to the library)

We’ll be outdoors enjoying the weather, sharing ice cream, and most importantly connecting as a group.

**We need your help and your ideas as we grow into the next phase of action together.**

At our last meeting, you helped us identify the issues that matter most—locally and nationally. Now it’s time to dig deeper and ask:

**What can we do about them?**

This meeting will focus on brainstorming next steps, expanding our impact, and dreaming up what sustained, powerful civic action can look like in our group.

Whether you’ve been showing up for rallies, making calls to your reps, or just following along, this is your invitation to help shape what comes next.


### 🧺 Small Act, Big Impact: Let’s Hit 100 Cans!
 We’re partnering with the Raging Grannies to collect **100 canned or shelf-stable food items** for local food banks like **Nancy’s Hope** and **Interfaith**.

✨ Bring one (or more!) items to the meeting—The Grannies will take care of the rest.
 
It’s an easy, meaningful way to contribute to our community. Let’s do this together!

### 📌 Meeting Details

**Location:**

 Heaven for Kids Park
 480 Greenley Road
 Sonora, CA 95370

**Date & Time:**

 Thursday, May 22
 5:30–7:00 PM

**Accessibility Notes:**

- Restrooms available next door at the public library (until 6pm)

- Wheelchair-friendly and level entry

- Water fountains on-site


👋 What to Bring:

- ✅ A can (or two) for the food drive

- ✅ Your ideas

- ☑️ Optional: Chair and/or mosquito repellent

🍨 What We’ll Provide:

- Ice cream

- Napkins & trash bags

- Pens & paper for brainstorming

📝 Agenda Highlights:

- Welcome + Executive Team Announcements

- Endorsements 101: What does it mean for our group?

- Group brainstorming: Future actions that matter

- Breakout conversations by topic

- And of course… ice cream time!


**In times like these, being in community helps us stay grounded, uplifted, and focused for the long haul.**

We can’t wait to see you there.

Warmly,
Your Tuolumne County Indivisible Team

title: Moms Next Door: Session #4 - Organizing Strategies
description:
Join us on Tuesday, June 17, 2025, on Zoom for the next session in our Moms Next Door program. Our digital lives and moves have never been tracked and utilized more to squash dissent and democracy – it’s time to go back to the basics of original offline organizing, or as we like to call it: Analog Organize. We’ll be skilling up and getting creative with offline tactics and tools to bring together community and build resistance. We will also be introducing the new MomsRising Organizing Platform as an alternative online tool to organize and mobilize in your communities.

Learn more about Moms Next Door and sign up for the monthly Dispatch, where we will share information, education, and resources to workshop how we will create change together, at https://www.momsrising.org/MomsNextDoorDispatch
